EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 042300 UTC
A LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM LIES TO THE N OF THE BRITISH ISLES AND MOVS AWAY
TO THE NE BY SATURDAY MORNING. A TROUGH MOVS IN FM THE SW ON SATURDAY MORNING
AND MOVS N ACROSS THE AREA ON SATURDAY AFTERNOON. THE TOUGH DEVELOPS A LOW
PRESSURE CENTRE AND REMAINS SLOW MOV OVER SEA AREAS BAILEY FAEROES AND SE
ICELAND BY SATURDAY EVENING. AN ATLANTIC LOW EXTENDS A TROUGH WHICH MOVS
N ACROSS THE AREA FM MONDAY AFTERNOON MOV OVER THE FAR N BY MONDAY EVENING.
STRG TO NEAR GALE WINDS DEVELOP FM THE W SATURDAY MORNING. GALES ARE POSS
IN THE FAR NW AND S FM SATURDAY AFTERNOON. THESE STRG WINDS WITH EMBEDDED
GALES WILL SPREAD THROUGHOUT THE REGION SATURDAY AFTERNOON BUT EASING IN
THE S BY EVENING. STRG TO NEAR GALE WINDS WILL DEVELOP AGAIN IN THE FAR N
AND S OF THE REGION BY LATE SUNDAY MORNING WITH GALES AT TIMES IN THE FAR
N BY SUNDAY AFTERNOON.
